 Jefferys Bay - The Kouga Local Municipality on Wednesday urged people, who feel they might be showing the signs and symptoms of a Coronavirus (COVID-19) infection to contact the Humansdorp Hospital. "Kouga residents who are experiencing possible symptoms of the coronavirus (Covid-19) can phone the Humansdorp Hospital to set up an appointment to be screened and tested, if necessary," the municipality said. "The hospital has made available a dedicated line for this purpose - 042 200 4243. "Current symptoms reported for patients with Covid-19 include mild to severe respiratory illness with a dry cough, sore throat, shortness of breath or fever (38 degrees or higher)." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 